-- South Korean won jumps over 2 pct on Citi report
-- 
-- Sun Feb 22, 2009 10:06pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/02/23/us-markets-korea-forex-citi-sb-idUSTRE51M11320090223

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - The South Korean won jumped more than 2 percent against the dollar on Monday and local shares rose following a report that the U.S. government may buy up to 40 percent of Citigroup's common stock. 

 Investors also remained cautious over possible dollar-selling intervention by South Korea's foreign exchange authorities, supporting the won The local currency was quoted at 1,486.7/0.2 per dollar as of 0300 GMT, compared with Friday's domestic close of 1,506.0. The won has strengthened to as firm as 1,473.9. Seoul shares rose 2.21 percent. (Reporting by Cheon Jong-woo; Editing by  Ken Wills )